Name: HuskyHuskie
AboutMe:
One of the technical leads at my company asked me "so do you consider yourself a .NET developer?" My response was simply, I consider myself a developer. I don't have any favorite programming language, whatever can get the job done is what I go with. To elaborate on that in my current position I have my hand in several C# (.NET) projects while also being the main resource for Android development. On my own personal projects I still end up using PHP and MySQL as my back-end with Angular being my new obsession for front-end development. While I don't consider myself an expert in any particular area I would say I'm most confident working with Android and databases (preferably MySQL, but any kind of SQL will do).

In my free time when I'm not building my own applications I'm either reading a book or getting lost in the city or in a park. I consider myself a workaholic though.
